# Next.js 16 — read the local docs first

This repo runs Next.js 16.2.6. Your training data likely predates breaking
changes. Before writing or editing files under `app/`, read the relevant guide
in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.

## Hard rules

- Server Components are the default; mark Client Components with `"use client"`
  only when state, effects, or browser APIs are needed.
- Do not invent APIs from older Next.js versions (e.g. `getServerSideProps`,
  `pages/` routing, `next/head`).
- Use `metadata` exports for `<head>` content; never render `<head>` manually.
- Honor every deprecation notice you see in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.

## Cite the doc

In your PR description or final message, include the path you read:
`node_modules/next/dist/docs/<file>.md`. Reviewer will reject silent guesses.
